    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_88103">*snipping as appropriate, I know most of this wasn't aimed my way*<br />
<br />
Quote:Nerf bards? Hell yes. Just because I am so god damn tired of them lording it over us.<br />
<br />
When a class starts selling PLing services on stormhammer en masse for RL cash.<br />
I believe you're referring to the massive AE kites in HoH that Worry did.  Yep, that was wrong.  It was unbalanced.  The trick itself was fine, completely legal.  It was the zone itself that was put together that worked perfectly for it.  The zone was changed, that trick is no longer possible there.  If PLing people for cash is wrong, though... aiming that particular argument at bards when druids and shamans have been doing it for a long time seems a bit misplaced.<br />
<br />
Quote:When a class can swarm kite groups of 20 mobs for more then one AA per hour.<br />
I have never met a bard that can get one AA per hour swarm kiting.  It's good, but it's not THAT good.  Lag, mob availability, pathing, and weird factors would make such a kite very, very difficult to pull off.  Not impossible, I suppose, but that would be an hour of damned hard work, great FT gear, an instaclick invis item (only 2 in-game, both are very rare/expensive)and perfection in technique.<br />
<br />
Quote:Can have their choice of guilds even with only moderate skill level.<br />
Relative to other classes, how much skill do the other classes take?  There are a few tricks to each class, but no class is as tricky to play right as the bard.  No class is as hard to play, physically.  Twisting, knowing what songs to play and when, and knowledge of songs and how to use them... there's a lot to playing a bard.  <br />
<br />
Quote:Own skills deemed gamebreaking when they were removed from other classes (memwipe).<br />
Well, I assume you refer to the monk's FD ability.  That has a refresh of what, 10 seconds?  Bards, even the ones with uber gear and AA's, can only sustain one FM every 5-10 minutes.  So yes, it was gamebreaking when it went along with FD.  But the checks on its use for bards are enough, I think, to permit its use.<br />
<br />
Quote:If you don't want to be nerfed, stop idiotic, stupid, self serving posts like this on non bard boards.<br />
Um, it's just a discussion.  What have I said that is idiotic and stupid?<br />
<br />
Quote:Now that you have all successfully turned monks against you have you begun your campaign to annoy the rogues?<br />
Eh?  What exactly is it that's eating you?  If you want to talk about fixing monks vs nerfing bards, I can start a similar thread on Monkly business.  <br />
<br />
Quote:With bards like this fellow I quoted speaking for you, that is exactly what will happen.<br />
<br />
Perhaps you'd be happier taking my views as more the norm of bards than Thott.  We're not all uber guild-leaders, you know.<br />
<br />
Quote:But I wish they would stop kicking sand in the face of pure melee. A nerf is needed as much for game balance as it is for humility.<br />
I fail to see how we are unbalanced.  Humility... well, I think that's something on the human side, not the software side, that could use some adjustment.  Keep in mind, we are bards; we like to show off.<br />
<br />
Quote:I just have this image in my head of a bard swarm kiting 20 mobs past a group of a monk, warrior, rogue and cleric (who are single pulling) and shout taunts to us about how we are overpowered.<br />
If I could draw I'd make a cartoon out of it and stick it in every bard whining post I could find.<br />
<br />
20 mobs?  That I'd like to see.  More than 7 or 8 and they spread too much and some will keep coming after you.  If they all pounce on your pet, then your pet may die too fast, and poof, you get no xp. Swarm kiting is weird.  <br />
<br />
It's also easy for things beyond your control to mess you up on a swarm kite.  If a mob spawns on you and stuns you, or wanders into you, you're dead.  If you get a lag spike, you're dead.  If someone decided to sit down nearby and watch you kite, they're dead, and you could quite possibly be next.  If someone tries to KS or &quot;help&quot; you by snaring the mobs, they might go the wrong way, and you're dead.  If the mobs path in a way you don't expect, you're dead.  If there's a caster mob that adds, you're toast.  If you mis-time an invis, your pet will poof, and you'll get no experience.  If your pet breaks charm at an awkward time, you can lose track of where it is, and your swarm will not swarm your pet, but come after you.<br />
<br />
Swarm kiting is intense.  It requires rivetted attention, skill, knowledge, and good timing.  Single-pulling to a melee group requires putting on auto-attack, adjusting your position, and an occasional heal.  It seems resonable to me that swarming should allow more reward for the time put in than a group situation where you sit in the same spot, since it is higher-risk and more difficult.<br />
<br />
Quote:Unless you directly define &quot;powerful&quot; as &quot;needed in raid&quot;, no the most powerful class is not clerics, at least not according to your lame reason.<br />
Good point.  Power is more than the demand and need for a given class.  Even so, the things cited about us bards that need nerfing, according to posts on this thread, are ones that make us desired to group with over other classes.  Clerics have some of the ultimate trump cards for both groups and raids, across the level ranges.  It's not a point I brought up, but there is a certain similarity.<br />
<br />
Quote:Telling people to go play another class is just ignoring the problem, just as the SOE staff is doing now, not fixing it. If people said nothing or just went to play other classes nothing would ever be changed and everyone would be wondering why pure melee would have the lowest amount of active toons. <br />
Amen.  The powers that be do read these boards from time to time.  These threads often spur questions at fan fairs, feedback in-game, etc.  Hence, me starting this thread.  I saw a lot of irrational mud-slinging over class balance, and thought that some cooler heads could provide some more constructive insight.  Only two or three of the posters here are letting their anger dictate their posts, so far, so good.<br />
<br />
Quote:Well, how many classes can haste, Haste beyond the existing cap, increase spell damage, buff multiple stats, slow, mez, pull, increase multiple resists by 100+, debuff resists, dot, DD, snare, regen hp, regen mana, charm, DA, and mana drain? All without mana?<br />
It's true, no other class has our versatility, or our partial independence from mana.  But in the interest of fairness, how many classes have virtually all their buffing, debuffing, hastes, slows, and DoT spells last for 15 seconds?  We can do any of those things, but we cannot do all of those things, because we can only fill one role at a time. There are drawbacks to our versatility.  Cheif among them, we generally aren't as good as others at their prescribed specialties.  We can haste pretty darn well, but a shaman can haste, buff like mad, regen, slow, and heal in one fight, thanks to the long duration of his spells.<br />
<br />
I love metaphors, so here's mine.<br />
<br />
We are the swiss army knives of EQ; you can use maybe a couple tools at a time.  The rest have to stay locked away until you fold in the ones you're using.<br />
<br />
You still are going to want an axe to chop up wood.  Melee classes are like that; you all are the pros of chopping stuff up.  Right now, that axe is dull, and needs sharpening. <br />
<br />
I'm all for monks, rogues, and warriors getting some serious props.  I just don't see why implicit in melee balance is bard nerfage.  <br />
<br />
Quote:If they gave Warriors an AC/ATK debuff like a bard song (and high agro), <br />
This is already in the game, with good proccing weapons.  There are better ways of doing it, though, I agree.  Crippling blows of some sort could help.  Swing for the legs to snare the mob, hitting the arms to slow him... yeah, that would be cool.<br />
<br />
Quote:Monks a group Regen/mana regen 'aura' like a bard song, <br />
Heck, yeah!  Who's supposed to be masters of meditation, anyway?  The kung-fu masters!  That's a great idea.  You could have it be a group meditation thing, where if the monk sits and meditates with the casters, they get mana regeneration.  Great downtime reducer, and it wouldn't break raid-type scenarios, where monks would be needed for DPS in the big fights.<br />
<br />
I've always thought of kung fu masters as being fellas who can disable and mess up an opponent, not just pounding them.  Again, crippling attacks would be pretty cool.  They could be skill-based or &quot;mana&quot; based, whatever<br />
<br />
Quote:and rogues a 50% Slow/dot ability, again like a bard song, <br />
I've mentioned the idea before, I think that rogues should get drugs/poisens that do things besides DoTs, like slows, debuffs, roots, snares, buff stripping, and mana drain.<br />
<br />
Sorry for the long reply, thought I'd get several done in one post.<br />
 </div>
