    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_88106">Goood morning, happy hangover to all who went out last night  <br />
<br />
Um. A couple of points:<br />
#1) FM is 900 mana, I believe, not 400<br />
#2) Fading 2-3 times in 5 seconds requires a mana pool of 2700 or higher, that's all. Sure, it will be a while till they get it back*<br />
#3) The power of fade is in the no-fail instant memwipe - avoiding reagro afterwards is pretty much a matter of skill, invis component or no.<br />
#4) I label bards the most powerful class not because of what they bring to raids (where they can mana pump groups or the entire raid, shield the entire raid with resists, improve damage dealers offensive power, or give the main tank a helluva damage shield... oh, and pull too, note Thott's continued requests/historic revisions indicating that they are &quot;a pulling class&quot; on top of everything else) but because they can do the most solo or grouped. I can invite a bard and have him take on any of 5-6 roles of the 7-8 that exist in game in my group. On raids, same dealie. That's an awful lot of power. Clerics, not so much, although they're a lot more powerful than most people give them credit for - they can do a lot more than heal. In fact most classes can do a lot more than their 'role X' other than ... pure melee!Quote:And all of that is balanced by the fact that bards can only do 3 things reliably at any given time, usually only 1-2 during raids.Yeah, Thott tried to make the same argument a few times. Obviously bards deserve Rez and CH since they can't do more than 3 things at once, by that logic...<br />
<br />
Anyhow, this is indeed a rogue board...<br />
<br />
- Ssarvhok<br />
<br />
<br />
* Note I've suggested Fade get changed to 300 mana, 1 minute recast, 15% fail rate, which would even without AA or FT get normal bards a Fade every 30 min, and get top end bards a fade ever 1.6 min. <br />
<br />
 </div>
