    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_88107">For those of you who missed it, there already was a nerf to bard swarmkiting.  I assure you, bards and enchanters didn't.<br />
<br />
They changed charmed-mob aggro so that if a mob has 4 or more characters on the hate list, it ignores the charmed mob and goes right for the bard or enchanter or whoever's on top of the hate list.<br />
<br />
From a practical standpoint, that means that bards and enchanters can only charm-solo (swarmkiting is a form of charm soloing) in an empty area.  So much as a single group close by and the swarm is all over the soloist.  (BTW, the esteemed poster who spoke of bards running a swarm past a group and thumbing their nose is, frankly, a bit off.  The bard doesn't have time for that kind of nonsense if he's swarmkiting, and if this did happen the bard's swarm went out of control and he died soon after.)<br />
<br />
I thought this an elegant solution, myself.  Unused zones are available for the bard or enchanter to play in without hurting anyone else; the moment another group zones in the bard MUST negotiate or leave.  However, some folk apparently want more taken away from the bard, even on as small a thing as XPing.<br />
<br />
It's been noted above that bards are at the bottom of the list on number played.  Before the call for the nerf bat gets any louder, consider the number of guild and raid events that depend on the dwindling number of high-level bards.  If bards are nerfed to the point that no-one wants to play them any more (and just doing to Fading Memories what was done to Manaburn could accomplish the feat) and the next time you need that resist-boosting, mana-pumping swiss army knife - he may not be around.  I'll be leveling a toon that's useful, myself.<br />
<br />
Raivenn Lunatic<br />
Bard<br />
 </div>
