    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_88111">Quote:#4) I label bards the most powerful class not because of what they bring to raids (where they can mana pump groups or the entire raid, shield the entire raid with resists, improve damage dealers offensive power, or give the main tank a helluva damage shield... oh, and pull too, note Thott's continued requests/historic revisions indicating that they are &quot;a pulling class&quot; on top of everything else) but because they can do the most solo or grouped. I can invite a bard and have him take on any of 5-6 roles of the 7-8 that exist in game in my group. On raids, same dealie. That's an awful lot of power. Clerics, not so much, although they're a lot more powerful than most people give them credit for - they can do a lot more than heal. In fact most classes can do a lot more than their 'role X' other than ... pure melee!<br />
<br />
What 5-6 roles can a bard take on in your group?  I can serve as a puller, tank, crowd control, haster, DPS, debuffer, slower, or buffer.  I can do two of these fairly reliably in a group situation.  Not 5 or 6.  When I crowd control, I'm not pulling.  When I'm tanking, I'm not hasting or slowing.  And for each of these roles, except pulling, there are better classes than mine out there for those roles.  We can do the most, but we can't do the best.<br />
<br />
Regards to your pure melee one-dimensionality, I completely agree; melee classes need some retuning with respect to the other classes and their expanded and broadened abilities.<br />
<br />
Quote:Yeah, Thott tried to make the same argument a few times. Obviously bards deserve Rez and CH since they can't do more than 3 things at once, by that logic...<br />
Thott said THAT?  Wow!  Why do you all take him so seriously?  I mean... that's so ridiculous; it's trolling.  Yes, we are limited by being able to do no more than 3 songs at once.  That's a good limitation to have, one that balances us well, even if it does make playing bards pretty demanding, click-wise.  Rezzes and complete heals... wow.  I gotta find where he said that.<br />
<br />
Quote:You'd be surprised how many folks consider XPing to be a bit more than &quot;a small thing&quot; /agree.<br />
<br />
Quote:I see more and more high level bard twinks now adays, heck even I have one, why pass up all that power!<br />
You have a high-level twink?  Aside from that being an oxymoron, how do you see bards as such a power class?<br />
<br />
Quote:They changed charmed-mob aggro so that if a mob has 4 or more characters on the hate list, it ignores the charmed mob and goes right for the bard or enchanter or whoever's on top of the hate list.<br />
This is not the case anymore, though some mobs, even social ones, won't swarm if a swarm is very large.  The real swarming nerf came by making our charm song last longer and cost more mana.<br />
