    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_88122">Quote:I do not understand why people take him and his writings so seriously. It's one guy, writing articles that, while rather insensitive, and not always as precise and logical as perhaps they could be, tend to be fairly well thought-out. Thott is not our leader. He's not our elected representative. The only viewpoint he represents is the top-end raiding perspective. There's a lot more to the game than that.There has been precedent for this. Furor of FoH has been instrumental in  having the Monk's mitigations abilities nerfed. His posts highlighting CERTAIN high end raiding monks' ability to &quot;tank better than a warrior&quot; has been pretty influential in getting the nerf bat out on the entire class. Like it or not, Thott seems to be positioning himself as the &quot;Furor&quot; of his class (somewhat in reverse). He is doing his damnest to downgrade the monk class's FD pulling abilities and positioning the bard classes' pulling ability as natural and inherent to it in an attempt to stave off a nerf.<br />
<br />
Frankly I am all a bit fed up with all of this. Each class is trying to its best to hide as much of it's ability as much as possible so that the big bad bully (SOE) won't notice and take away their toys. <b>Quellious Moonlite Knights </b><br />
Greif 65 Coercer : Stuffs of Nonsense.<br />
Baene 52 Attack Disciple! : Tools of Evil!<br />
Feare 40 ShadowKnight : Heavy Tanking.<br />
<br />
<i>&quot;Classes are not that out of balance&quot; -AbsorEQ... and Bozo the clown</i> <br />
 <br />
Which Street Fighter are you? <br />
Test by Nathan</div>
